{
  "Election": {
    "election_id": "7f4f7q",
    "title": "BV2194 — Bullet Voting Backfires (2 of 2) — the strategic ballots elect the nightmare",
    "description": "From the exercises set of the STAR education repo (github.com/masiarek/star-voting-library, 01_STAR/exercises/) — predict-then-peek problems with hidden solutions; this election is the live, vote-able copy of its exercise. The strategy pair's payoff (exercise ex06): identical to BV2193 except Ari's four fans now BULLET VOTE — Ari 5, Bree 0, Cash 0 — hoping to drag Ari past the compromise. It works halfway: Bree crashes 25 -> 13 and out of the runoff, and Ari (20) becomes a finalist. But the runoff Ari inherits is against Cash (21), and zeroing Bree never manufactured a single Ari-over-Cash preference: Cash wins 5-4. The fans demoted their sure second choice and elected their zero. Under honest ballots (BV2193) they had Bree; the gamble bought Cash. The ranked races agree — with Bree's support hidden, IRV and Ranked Robin elect Cash too. STAR's runoff is exactly the feature that makes bullet voting a risk, not a free lift. LH-verified.",
